This paper deals with semantic segmentation using deep convolutional neural networks, which is a topic closely related to computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a new regularization technique that involves learning to regress the distance transform, which is a technique that can be applied to a wide range of deep learning models and is therefore relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves training a multi-task model, which is a common technique in neural networks and therefore relevant to neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Finally, the paper involves post-processing of segmentation results, which is a topic that is relevant to natural language processing (cs.CL) as well.
